The '''Lexas systems''' were a group of [[Star system/Legends|star systems]]<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> that shared its name with the [[Lexas Prime system/Legends|Lexas Prime system]], a part of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories']] [[Kessel sector/Legends|Kessel sector]].<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> At some point by [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'' represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> several petty [[Crime lord/Legends|crimelords]] operated in the Lexas systems. The [[Krish (species)/Legends|Krish]] [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Karalan]] worked for the crimelords but became progressively more indebted to them. After Karalan lost his [[Starship/Legends|starship]] and was almost [[Death/Legends|killed]] by a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]], the Krish instead became a member of the [[Mytaranor Slaving Council]].<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Lexas systems were mentioned in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="AIR" />

